VCSC News
August 31 at 3:47 PM ·

REMINDER

VCSC Early Release is tomorrow (9/1). This means that HS/MS students will be released at 1pm and elementary students will be released at 1:30pm. For your planning, the first Tuesday of each month is an early release day. We will make sure to remind you of each early release day as well on our social media sites and our website. Thank you for your time.

Also, with Homecoming being moved, we will not be having an early release on Friday, September 25th.

Vincennes Lincoln Volleyball
August 22 at 6:12 PM ·

The Vincennes Lincoln volleyball teams traveled to Southridge today. 💚🏐💚

The Varsity team won in straight sets. 25-14, 25-14, 25-19. The Alices are 3-0 on the season and will play Castle at home on Tuesday.

Leaders
Kills
Maycee Lange 12
Livie Koenig 9

Assists
Callie Foster 33

Digs
Kali Haynes 5
Mackenzie Newland 4

Aces
Maycee Lange 4

The JV won in 2 sets. 25-9, 25-19
They are 3-0 on the season.

Leaders
Kills
Zoey Weiss 9

Assists
Jaclyn Sutton 9
Gracie Kramer 7

Digs
Olivia Hamilton 12
Cameron Cary 9

Aces
Cameron Cary 4

The freshman team opened their season today. They played well and fought hard but came up short in 3 sets. 20-25, 25-20, 7-15.

Leaders
Kills
Mattye Meadows 8
Xzandra Cox 7

Assists
McKenna Henderson 14

Digs
Courtney Deffendoll 8

Aces
Mattye Meadows 3

All three teams will play Castle at home on Tuesday.

#bumpkill #coachpoint #jumpball #showemwhoisboss #teamfirst #effort #werisetogether #maskup

Vincennes Lincoln Tennis
August 18 at 11:47 PM ·

LHS Tennis Parents and fans,

I would like to thank those of you who wore masks and socially distanced while attending our match on Monday. Please know that even though we play outside face coverings and social distancing are still requirements per IHSAA and VCSC policy. Our team wears them anytime we’re not on the court, and we should have the same expectations for those attending our events. The more we adhere to this policy, the greater our chances of your child having a full tennis season. Thank you for your continued support of LHS tennis!

- Coach Crane

The VCSC Re-Entry Plan has been updated to accommodate the Governor's new Executive Order mandating face masks/coverings. Face masks/coverings will be needed for students grade 3 and up and all staff. Exemptions laid out in the Governor's Executive Order can be found here (https://www.in.gov/gov/files/Executive%20Order%2020-37%20Face%20Covering%20Requirement.pdf). Additional questions can be sent to our helpline (vcschelp@vcsc.k12.in.us). Thank you for your understanding and patience as we all work through these changes together.

https://docs.google.com/document/d/15hMZjHR72pSVJIiDefnys8074GdQYr9wFEbMW-ForIM/edit

post_text:
VCSC Update for 7-17-2020

There is a lot of good news as we move closer to the beginning of school. Our community is in a very good position for reentry on August 6th. As you know, all plans are subject to change but we have a strong foundation with our VCSC Reentry Plan that will allow us to overcome anything and everything. Next week, we will be sending out a survey of interest in virtual at-home learning. This is different than our eLearning and will be a program, self paced that will be done at home by the student. While we believe in person learning is best for our students and community, our goal is to provide platforms for our students if in person instruction isn’t an option. We thank you for all your patience and understanding as we go through this together. Have a great weekend.

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wiWc0Clw68U

post_text: Congratulations Mrs. Niehaus!
shared_text:
Knox County Chamber Of Commerce
June 17 at 4:30 PM ·

The Knox County Chamber of Commerce is proud to announce the 2020 Educator of the Year is Tina Niehaus. She has been a teacher for 32 years, having spent 29 of those years teaching first grade at Tecumseh-Harrison Elementary School in Vincennes.

The Educator of the Year is for a teacher or administrator working in a Knox County K-12 public or private school system. The recipient was selected based on years of service, accomplishments in the profession and endearment from students and other educators.

Tina shows her dedication to her education profession through being a leader in innovation within her classroom. Co-workers have said they admire Tina because of her open mindset and her end visions is always on the kids they serve.

Tina will be recognized on Friday, June 19, 2020 at noon through a virtual Facebook event on the Knox County Chamber of Commerce's Facebook page.

REMINDER: Food Distribution is on TUESDAY (May, 26th) this week. Time (9 am-11 am) and places (all VCSC elementary schools) of distribution will be the same.

Food Distribution will continue on Monday, and the following Mondays of the summer, starting on June 1st. There will be no deliveries during the summer. Anyone (family, friend, neighbor, etc.) can pick up food for a student, as long as we have a name.

Calling Everyone Stuck at Home!

Please join us for the First Virtual Camporee from the Buffalo Trace Council. Scouts of all ages are invited to attend. Not a Scout but wanting to learn more? You are invited to attend as well! We will have some online activities as well as activities you can do with your families; all in the comfort of your home.

Location: Your home and online
Date: May 9, 2020
Time: 8:00 am – 9:00 pm CT

An exciting day has been planned for you and your family. It is designed to be fun and interactive. We want to provide all of you with an opportunity to interact with other scouts. All Scouts (Cub Scouts, Scouts BSA, and Venturers) are encouraged to attend, we have activities for all ages.

This event will be free for all to attend, but you must register. Event patches will be optionally available after the event for $5 and will be mailed directly to you.

See link below to register and please check your email in the following days for more information as well.

https://scoutingevent.com/156-CabinFeverCamporee

post_text:
Good morning all,

I certainly know that many of you are dealing with larger issues this morning from the storm. It is an E-Learning or counted day for education in the VCSC but this is secondary and quite frankly if it does not occur today, it does not occur.

Many of you are without power and this includes many of our staff members as well and they simply may not be available during the hours of 9AM to 2PM.

As we have learned with Covid-19, we have to be flexible. We just did not know that today that Covid-19 would become secondary for many of us and our attention would turn elsewhere and with this we must be flexible today and patient as we have too many people dealing with much larger issues than that of education and this is primarily related to the storm from last night.

Hopefully we will slowly start to return to what is the new normal for the time being, but today, education is far more secondary.

Hope you all are safe and with this, please stay safe!

Mr. Parsley

Sodexo Nutrition Vincennes Community Schools
March 29 at 4:03 PM ·

Tomorrow we are distributing food from 9am-11am at Tecumseh, Riley, WCC, Vigo and Lincoln. We are trying to do this the safest way possible. Please open trunks or hatches on cars so we don't have to make direct contact. Also, if you are on the delivery list, please don't also go pick up at a school. If you are able to pick up please let us know so that we can give your delivery spot to someone who really needs it. Lastly, we are packing products to the best of our ability while dealing with delivery and product availability restraints. We do not have the means to customize meals based on the childs likes and dislikes. Thank you.

Important Announcement from Mr. Parsley

VCSC Superintendent
March 13 at 5:41 PM ·

Please listen to this important announcement from Mr. Parsley.

If you have additional questions and/or concerns, please feel free to contact us anytime on our VCSC Helpline. (vcschelp@vcsc.k12.in.us or 812-882-6376)

Additional information will be released on our social media sites, our website and through SchoolMessenger.

Quick Points:
• Week of March 16th is Spring Break
• Week of March 23rd VCSC students will have educational opportunities available through eLearning.
• Week of March 30th VCSC students will be eLearning.
• Week of April 6th VCSC students return.
• Packets will be provided for those without eLearning capabilities.
• We are currently finalizing a plan for food service on the weeks of March 23rd and March 30th. Final information will be released early next week.

THESE PLANS ARE TENTATIVE AND SUBJECT TO CHANGE.

shared_text:
The Online Alice
March 10 at 5:45 PM ·

FYI: Parents of current juniors/incoming seniors: If you would like your student to receive state-required immunizations at LHS by Knox County immunization staff, please return the vaccination interest forms to the Lincoln school nurse by the end of this week. This will be done in April and interest forms were mailed home last week. If you return the form, we will send home further consent and insurance forms that will be required for your student to have these shots done at school. If you do NOT return these forms, we will not be able to vaccinate your student at LHS. You would then need to set up an appointment at the Immunization Clinic or with your doctor to have these immunizations done prior to the 2020-2021 school year. Please contact the school nurse if you have any questions. Thank you!

VCSC KG REG 2033

VCSC News
March 4 at 7:04 PM ·

VCSC Kindergarten Registration is HERE, with an early online option!

On Tuesday, March 10th from 4pm-6:30pm all VCSC elementary schools will be hosting kindergarten registration.

To register your child, please go to the school district that your child lives in. Yes, you will still need to go to the school on registration day EVEN IF YOU FILL OUT THE INFORMATION ONLINE.

To find what district you live in, please click on the link and enter your address.

Find my district: https://sites.google.com/vcsc.k12.in.us/vcsc-elementary-school-distric/home?fbclid=IwAR1vxmvX0_U75chcMjES5ho_Qxtymd0prqP3XL4ywdVCj9l7UeFmd5YcmRc

Please bring your child’s birth certificate, immunization records, and proof of address.

Your child must be 5 years old by August 1, 2020.

Online Kindergarten Registration: https://sites.google.com/vcsc.k12.in.us/vcsc-kg-reg-2033/home

We can’t wait to see you!

Vincennes Lincoln Lady Alices Basketball
February 12 at 7:35 PM ·

CONGRATULATIONS to senior Point Guard Darrian Carmean & junior post Maycee Lange on being selected Big 8 All-Conference by the Big 8 Coaches.

The Lady Alices claimed the final Big 8 Conference Championship with a 5-0 league mark.

Darrian led the Big 8 Conference in each of the following categories:
-Scoring at 21.4 PPG
- 3pt makes with 69 of 158
- Free throw makes with 130 of 152
- Free Throw percentage at 86%
- total assists with 82

Maycee was at or near the top of the Big 8 in:
- double doubles with 10
- 2nd in rebounds with 9.9 RPG
- 5th in scoring at 15.7 PPG
- 2nd in blocked shots with 41

Want to know why Lillian was embarrassed for me? Watch The Best Me with Mrs. V posted below to find out. It might have something to do with a silly joke I told. 😄

Students had the opportunity to start the new year out right by making the day of a classmate. They were inspired by the New Year Party Cracker and the fun contents inside. They wrote a compliment to a classmate in their homeroom on a party cracker cutout, included a joke and treat, and then presented them with it!

Thank you to Mrs. Hess’s class for inviting me to their homeroom so I could participate with them! I enjoyed watching everyone show kindness and have fun!

post_text: The Battle of the Badges is the FRIDAY (December 20th) from 10am to 8pm in front of Walmart. Join us to help the VPD and the VFD raise money for our local Salvation Army. In the end, our community is the winner. Thanks VPD and VFD!
shared_text:
Big Green Media
December 18, 2019 at 3:13 PM ·

When Officer Helderman came to Mr. Lang looking for some help on spreading the word about this competition for a great cause, he could not wait to get started.

4 years ago the Vincennes Police Dept and Vincennes Fire Dept started a friendly competition of ringing bells to raise money for the Salvation Army. It is called the Battle of the Badges! We ring bells at Wal-Mart from 10-8. This year it is on Dec. 20th.

Thank you to the Big Green Media students who helped with this project! Make sure to like and share!

VCSC Giving Tuesday Opportunity 19

Sensory Needs project by Mrs. O'Dell

Mrs. O'Dell is looking for replacements to help with sensory issues. A cover for a 15lb weighted blanket (41X60) adds longevity to this item, not to mention it can be easily cleaned. Also, she is looking for a light-up bubble tube with a fake fish inside. While this might seem like an odd request, this has been a student favorite item and the one they have has been broken for some time.

If you are interested in giving, please email us at vcschelp@vcsc.k12.in.us for more information.

VCSC Giving Tuesday Opportunity 17

Pool Project by Mrs. Soderling

Mrs. Soderling would like to remind us of our corporation's Pass for a Pool Pass Campaign. Businesses and individuals donate money to the Franklin PTO earmarked for this project. We purchase Rainbow Beach pool passes to be given away in drawings for those students who pass IREAD in March and in the summer. Donations go to buy the punch passes that are given away in drawings at each school as an added incentive to work hard to pass.

If you are interested in giving, please email us at vcschelp@vcsc.k12.in.us for more information.

VCSC Giving Tuesday Opportunity 13

Art in History project by Ms. Smith

Ms. Smith wants to create opportunities for students to have a small replica piece of history in their hands. A hands on history kit cost $11.95 each and can be seen in the link below. In this project, students would research a time period, which creates opportunities to improve reading, writing, and presentation skills. The final piece would be recreating the replica piece.

Website: https://hands-onhistory.com/collections/world-history.

If you are interested in giving to this project, email us at vcschelp@vcsc.k12.in.us for more information.
